1. *Vojniče*, spremi se za borbu! (Soldier, get ready for battle!)
2. Ovaj *vojniče* je izgledao veoma hrabro tokom vojne parade. (This soldier looked very brave during the military parade.)
3. *Vojniče* je bio veoma disciplinovan i sledio je sve naredbe svog komandanta. (The soldier was very disciplined and followed all the orders of his commander.)
4. Pripadnici vojske su često nazivani *vojnicima*, a ne *vojnicima* ili *vojničama*. (Members of the military are often called soldiers, not soldieresses or soldierettes.)
5. Moramo da pošaljemo više *vojnika* u tu oblast da zaštite civilno stanovništvo. (We need to send more soldiers to that area to protect the civilian population.)
6. Komandant je imao poverenja u svog *vojnika* da će uspešno izvršiti svoj zadatak. (The commander had faith in his soldier that he would successfully carry out his mission.)
7. *Vojniku* je naređeno da čuva granicu tokom cele noći. (The soldier was ordered to guard the border all night.)
8. Svi *vojnici* su dobili novo oružje kako bi bili bolje opremljeni. (All soldiers received new weapons to be better equipped.)
9. *Vojnici* su se suočavali sa teškim uslovima tokom rata, ali su i dalje ostajali jaki i borili se. (Soldiers faced difficult conditions during the war, but they still remained strong and fought.)
10. *Vojnicima* se pruža pomoć u traženju posla nakon što se vrate sa služenja vojnog roka. (Soldiers are provided with assistance in finding jobs after they return from military service.)